title.title: Re-route for N133 bus service from 1 September 2007

texts: Residents of Streatham Vale will benefit from a night service for the first time, thanks to a re-routing of the N133 night bus service, starting on Saturday 1 September.
The route currently goes from Liverpool Street bus station to Tooting Broadway.

The night service is to be re-routed at Streatham High Road via Greyhound Lane, Streatham Vale, Greyhound Terrace, Rowan Road, Manor Road, Commonside East, Upper Green East, London Road and Raleigh Gardens, terminating at Mitcham.
The N133 will provide a new direct link between Mitcham and Central London, via Streatham.
Passengers travelling to Tooting Broadway are advised to use route 57 which began operating throughout the night on 30 June 2007.

{"template":"bulletlist","items":["Route 133, which operates during the day, remains unchanged","The N133 night service runs two buses per hour, operating from 00:45 to 03:45","Route 57 operates 24 hours a day, with two buses per hour at night"]}
